<FrameLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    xmlns:tools="http://schemas.android.com/tools"
    android:layout_width="match_parent"
    android:layout_height="match_parent"
    tools:context="admin.example.com.SubTopics.Prob.BALLS">

    <ScrollView
        android:layout_width="wrap_content"
        android:layout_height="wrap_content"
        android:focusable="false"
        android:visibility="visible">


        <RelativeLayout
            android:id="@+id/rl1"
            android:layout_width="match_parent"
            android:layout_height="wrap_content"
            android:layout_marginBottom="500dp"
            android:layout_marginEnd="2dp"
            android:layout_marginRight="4dp"
            android:layout_marginTop="30dp"
            android:minHeight="50dp">


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv1"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_toEndOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:layout_toRightOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 1:\nA, B and C enter into a partnership and their shares are in ratio 1/2 : 1/3 : 1/4, after 2 months, A withdraws half of his capital and after 12 months, a profit of Rs 1050 is divided among them. What is B’s share ?\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv11"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@+id/tv1"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_toEndOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:layout_toRightOf="@id/ivContactItem2"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution :\n

Ratio of investments =1/2 : 1/3 : 1/4 , LCM of 2, 3, 4 = 12 ,multiply ratios with 12 we get 6 : 4 : 3 , so,initial investment be 6x, 2x and 3x so, we can write: A : B :C
=(6x X 2 + 3x X 10 ) : (4x X 12) :(3x X 12) = 7:8:6\n
B’s share= (8/21) x 1050 = 400 \n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121" />

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div1"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv11" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv2"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div1"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 2:\n
P and Q invest in a business in the ratio 3 : 2. If 5% of the total profit goes to charity and P’s share is Rs. 855, the total profit is:\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv22"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv2"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Let the total profit be Rs. 100.\n
After paying to charity, A’s share = Rs. 95 x 3/5 = Rs. 57.\n
If A’s share is Rs. 57, total profit = Rs. 100.\n
If A’s share Rs. 855, total profit =(100/57) x 855 = 1500.\n\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div2"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv22" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv3"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div2"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 3:\n
A started a business with Rs. 21,000 and is joined afterwars by B with Rs. 36,000. After how many months did B join if the profits at the end of the year are divided equally?"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv33"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv3"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Let B joined after x months\n
Then, 21000 x 12 = 36000 x (12 – x)36 = 180x = 5Hence, B joined after 5 months\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div3"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv33" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv4"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div3"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 4.\n
Ashok being the sleeping partner receives 1/10th of profit and the remaining is divided between pramod and prakash in the ratio of 1:2..If the difference between the profit shares of Ashok and Prakash is Rs.2000.What is pramod’s share in Rs.?:"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv44"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv4"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
let total profit =x\n
ashok’s share in profit is (1/10)x\n
remaining profit = x= (1/10)x= (9/10)x\n
pramod’s share= 1/3 x (9/10)x = (3/10 )x\n
Prakash’s share= 2/3 x (9/10)x = (6/10)x\n
ashok – prakash= (6/10)x -(1/10)x = (5/10)x\n
5/10 x = 2,000 so, x= 4000\n
pramod’s share= (3/10) x 4000=1200\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div4"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv44" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv5"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div4"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 5.\n
Anju and Bimal are partners in a business. Anju contributes 1 / 4 of the capital for 15 months and Bimal received 2 / 3 of the profit, for how long Bimal’s money was used ? \n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv55"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv5"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Then Bimal’s share in profit= (2/3)x\n
so anju’s share in profit= x- (2/3)x =x/3\n
so,we get ratios of profit of Anju :Bimal :: 1:2\n
Let total capital invested be Rs P and Anju’s money was used for 15 months while Bimal’s money was used for b months .\n
then, (1/4)P X 15 divide by (3/4)P x b = 1/2 [ Capital x time =profit] so,we get b=10\n
Bimal’s money was used for 10 months\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div5"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv55" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv6"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div5"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 6.\nRoshan started a business by investing Rs.10,000. After 6 months Ahamed joined with him by investing Rs.16,000. At the end of 3 years they gained Rs.49000 then the share of Roshan is:
\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv66"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv6"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
The logic in Roshan invests Rs.10,000 for 3 years (36 months).\n
And Ahamed invests Rs.16,000 for 30 months. Then,\n
Roshan : Ahamed = (10,000 x 36) : (16,000 x 30)\n
36 : 16x3 = 12:16 = 3:4\n
Therefore,Roshan's share = Rs.(3/7 x 49,000) = Rs.21000\n
Hence the answer is Rs.21,000.\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div6"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv66" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv7"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div6"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 7.\n
Mathan started a business by investing Rs.18,000. After 5 months, Asha joined with him by investing Rs.16,000. If at the end of the year, they earn a profit of Rs.13,490 then Asha's share is:"                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv77"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv7"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Mathan invests Rs.18,000 for a year. (12 months).\n
And Asha invests Rs.16,000 for 7 months. Then,\n
Mathan : Asha = (18,000 x 12) : (16,000 x 7)\n
18x12 : 16x7 = 27:14\n
Therefore, Asha's share = Rs. 14/41 x 13,940 = Rs.4760,\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div7"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv77" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv8"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div7"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 8.\n
Mary and John started a business. Mary invests Rs.5000 for 16 months and John invests Rs.6000 for 20 months. If they earned a profit of Rs.4510 then the share of Mary is:\n"               android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv88"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv8"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text=" Solution :\nRatio of their shares = (5000x16) : (6000x20)
= 5x16 : 6x20\n
= 16 : 24 = 2:3\n
Then, Mary's share = Rs.(4510 x 2/5) = Rs.902 x 2 = Rs.1804\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div8"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv88" />

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv9"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div8"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 9.\n
Raj invested Rs 76000 in a business. After few months Monty joined him and invests Rs 57000. At the end of year both of them share the profits at the ratio of 2:1. After how many months Monty joined Raj ?"
                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv99"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv9"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Raj invested Rs 76,000 for 12 months and Monty invested Rs 57,000 for x months.\n

Now 76000 × 12 / 57000 × x = 2 :1\n

⇒ 76 × 12 / 2 = 57x\n

⇒ x = 8\n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div9"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv99" />


            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv10"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/div9"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Question 10.\n
A, B and C shared profits in ratio of 5:7:8. They partnered for 14 months, 8 months and 7 months respectively. What was he ratio of their investments ?
\n"                android:textColor="#212121"
                android:textStyle="bold"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"/>

            <TextView
                android:id="@+id/tv100"
                android:layout_width="wrap_content"
                android:layout_height="wrap_content"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv10"
                android:layout_marginLeft="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginStart="@dimen/activity_horizontal_margin"
                android:layout_marginTop="8dp"
                android:lineSpacingMultiplier="1.4"
                android:text="Solution –\n
Let X is the total investment\n

⇒14 x = 5\n
⇒ 8 x = 7\n
⇒ 7x = 8
\n
⇒ Final investment ratio = 20 : 49 : 64
\n\n \n"
                android:textAppearance="@style/TextAppearance.AppCompat.Medium"
                android:textColor="#212121"/>

            <include
                android:id="@+id/div10"
                layout="@layout/item_divider"
                android:layout_width="match_parent"
                android:layout_height="4dp"
                android:layout_below="@id/tv100" />


        </RelativeLayout>

    </ScrollView>


</FrameLayout>
